Part 3 — Qualification Leakage
Why Bad Qualification Creates Revenue Leakage

Revenue rarely leaks because salespeople forget to follow up.

More often, it leaks much earlier.

It leaks when the wrong opportunities enter the pipeline.

If poor-fit prospects are qualified as "good opportunities," every downstream metric becomes misleading.

Pipeline looks healthy.
Forecast looks optimistic.
Sales activity stays high.

But none of it converts into revenue.

By the time leadership realizes something is wrong, weeks—or even months—have already been lost.

What is Qualification Leakage?

Qualification Leakage happens when sales teams invest time in opportunities that were never likely to close.

Instead of filtering bad-fit accounts early, they move through the pipeline and consume valuable sales capacity.

Think of it as a water filter.

If the filter is broken, dirty water flows into the entire system.

Poor qualification works exactly the same way.

